<html><head><title>HELP PAGE</title></head><body><p><span style="font-weight:bold;">Q1. How to add widget to home screen?</span></p><p><span>A1.1&nbsp;</span>Long press an empty space on your home screen, then select "widgets" and load the widget list. Select Amber Weather widget with the right size from the list by tapping it.</p><p>A1.2 Enter the program drawer, then slide to"widgets", finally long press the "widget" and drag it the home screen.</p><p><span style="font-weight: bold;">Q2. Why does the clock on widget always freeze?</span></p><p>A2. Please make sure that you have enabled "Service Guard" in advanced settings.</p><p>If this doesn't work, please check that whether Amber Weather is in the White/Ignore List of some apps that may kill it. If you have apps like Task Killer, Service Manager, Battery Saver, Clean Master orGame Booster, please add Amber Weather into the White/Ignore List to keep widgets in sync.</p><p><span>If all these methods fail, please email to us:support@infolife.mobi. We will look into that and try our best to solve the problem.</span></p><p><span style="font-weight:bold;">Q3. Why do I get inaccurate temperature?</span></p><p><span>A3.</span>First, please reset your update interval.Please make sure that you have set the interval as 3 hours. We suggest you set it as an hour. (Go to Settings-General-Update Interval)</p><p><span>If you reset your update interval, but still get inaccurate weather data, please try other data sources in settings.(Go to Settings-General-Data Source)</span></p><p><span>If you try the methods above but still getwrong weather data, please email support@infolife.mobi, and tell us your location and the data sources you have tried.</span></p><p><span style="font-weight:bold;">Q4. Why can't I get my location?</span></p><p><span>A4.</span>Please enable GPS and other location services. You can also tap the re-locate button in city management to refresh your current location.&nbsp;</p><p><span style="font-weight:bold;">Q5. How to save battery?</span></p><p><span>A5.</span>If your widget or clock doesn't freeze, you can disable the "Service Guard" in advanced settings to save battery.(Go to Settings-Advanced Settings-Service Guard)</p><p><span style="font-weight:bold;">Q6. This app is not available in my mother language.</span></p><p><span>A6. Please join our translate project to localize this app for your country.</span></p><p></p><p><span style="font-weight:bold;">Q7.</span><strong>If I have more than 1 widget, how can I apply the skin?</strong></p><p>A7.Please first apply a widget to your home screen.(You can follow the method in Q8) Then tap the widget, and choose a different skin to apply.</p><p><span style="font-weight:bold;"></span></p><p><span style="font-weight:bold;">Q8. Wrong widget size?</span></p><p>A8. Please note that some widgets only work in specific sizes. So please match the size of your home screen with the size of the widget you want to apply.</p><p><span><span style="font-weight: bold; white-space: normal;">Q9. How can I change 24-hour clock to 12-hour clock?</span></span></p><p>A9. Please go to "Settings"-"Unit". Tap the clock in the middle, then you can switch 24-hour clock to 12-hour clock.</p><p><strong>Q10. Why can't I update weather conditions in the notification bar like before?</strong></p><p>A10. We've made some adjustments in the notification bar. At present, you can tap the weather icon next to temperature to update weather information.</p><p><br></p><!--!doctype--></body></html>
